post_text:
LISD elementary campuses to host virtual Meet the Teacher event

Laredo Independent School District elementary campuses will be hosting Meet the Teacher Event on Thursday, August 20, at 3:00 p.m. Schools are inviting parents to virtually visit their children’s classrooms during Meet the Teacher Event. Teachers will contact parents to provide them with their link for the virtual Meet the Teacher.

Elementary school principals and teachers will be able to introduce themselves and express their expectations for the new school year. Parents have the opportunity to meet their children’s teachers and learn what expectations they have set for their classes during the school year.

According to Myrtala Ramirez, LISD Director of Elementary Education parents will have an opportunity to meet their child’s teacher and ask questions prior to the first day of school.

The first day of school for LISD students is Monday, August 24.

post_text: Se ha ampliado el plazo para solicitar los beneficios alimentarios de la Transferencia Electrónica de Beneficios por Pandemia (P-EBT, por sus siglas en inglés) hasta el 21 de agosto. ¿Recibió su hijo comidas escolares gratuitas o a precio reducido a través del Programa Nacional de Almuerzos Escolares (National School Lunch Program) durante el año escolar 2019-2020? Si es así, su familia puede ser elegible para este beneficio alimentario único. Visite hhs.texas.gov/pebt para obtener más información sobre la P-EBT. Si tiene preguntas relacionadas con la elegibilidad o si necesita ayuda para presentar la solicitud, comuníquese con el Centro de Atención al Cliente de la P-EBT al 833-613-6220. La regla de carga pública no se aplica a los beneficios de la P-EBT.

post_text:
La Transferencia Electrónica de Beneficios por Pandemia (P-EBT, por sus siglas en inglés) es un beneficio de alimentos único para las familias que perdieron el acceso a comidas gratuitas o a precio reducido debido al cierre de las escuelas. A fin de mayo, las escuelas les enviarán instrucciones para realizar una solicitud a las familias elegibles para la P-EBT. La solicitud de la P-EBT estará disponible la primera semana de junio.
Los beneficios de alimentos de la P-EBT son para los niños que recibieron beneficios de alimentos del Programa Asistencial de Nutrición Suplementaria (SNAP, por sus siglas en inglés) para marzo de 2020 y para los niños que estén certificados para recibir comidas gratuitas o a precio reducido en Texas durante el año escolar 2019-20. Para obtener más información, visite: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

post_text:
Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures. Eligible P-EBT families will receive application instructions from schools in late May. The P-EBT application will open the first week of June.
P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

post_text: LISD added eight new transit buses to its fleet today. Sporting the LISD logo and logos for Garcia Early College, Martin, Nixon, and Cigarroa High Schools, the buses can transport up to 48 passengers. LISD Bus Driver Delia Flores drove the bus to the Superintendent's Office this morning. The new buses have all the latest safety features to transport children safely to their destinations. Shown from left are LISD Transportation Director Esteban Rangel, LISD Superintendent Dr. Sylvia G. Rios, Flores, LISD Board of Trustees Secretary Monica Garcia, and LISD Board of Trustees President Hector Noyola.

Nixon High School’s Coleman named U.S. Presidential Scholar

Vivian Coleman, a graduating senior at Nixon High School and the Vidal M. Trevino School of Communications and Fine Arts, has been named a 2020 U.S. Presidential Scholar by the U.S. Department of Education. Coleman, who is the Valedictorian for the Nixon High School Class of 2020, is one of 161 students nationally and one of four Texans selected on the basis of her scholastic achievement, artistic excellence, career preparation, demonstrated leadership ability, community service, strong character, and commitment to high ideals.

post_text:
No classes for LISD students on Monday, May 25

Laredo Independent School District campuses will be closed Monday, May 25, for staff development and training. LISD administration, faculty, and staff will meet virtually Monday for their required staff development training.

While teachers will not be connecting electronically with their students on Monday, May 25, students can still continue their at-home learning. Throughout the day, LISD employees will participate in professional development.

LISD’s free Grab and Go curbside meal service will be provided on Monday, May 25. Breakfast and lunch meals will be available for pick-up from 9:30 a.m. to 12 Noon at 25 LISD schools for students one to 18 years of age. Menu is subject to change upon availability of product.

Student and employees will resume their at-home learning schedules on Tuesday, May 26.

Laredo ISD les recuerda que siempre tosa o estornude en pañuelos desechables o en el codo y lávese las manos para disminuir la propagación del virus. ¡Mantente sano! #StayHomeTexas

Students Experiencing Homelessness
If your family lives in any of the following situations:
A homeless shelter
Motel or campground
Car, park, empty building, bus station
Doubled-up with other people due to economic hardship

Please contact our District Homeless Liaison at (956) 273-1264 for program services available to students and families and district and community resources.

Si su familia vive en cualquiera de las siguientes situaciones:
En un albergue
Motel o terreno campamento
En un automovil, edificio abandonado, estacion de autobus
Compartiendo la vivienda con otras personas debido a dificultad economica

Llame al (956) 273-1264

LISD Tax Office to remain closed until further notice

Due to the temporary closure of the school district, the LISD Tax Office will remain closed to the public until further notice.

LISD taxpayers have several options to pay their property tax. They can make online payments on the district’s webpage at https://www.laredoisd.org by scrolling all the way down in the section For Community and click on Tax Office and on the left margin click on Tax Inquiry/E-Payment. You can also type the following web address: https://laredoisd.go2gov.net/faces/search.jsp

Common symptoms of #COVID19 are fever, dry cough, & shortness of breath. If you have mild symptoms, call your doctor & #StayHome. If you develop serious symptoms, such as trouble breathing, pressure in the chest, or bluish lips or face, call your doctor & seek care immediately.

Los síntomas comunes de #COVID19 son fiebre, tos seca y dificultad para respirar.Si tiene síntomas leves, llame a su médico y quedate en casa.Si desarrolla síntomas graves, como dificultad para respirar o presión en el pecho, busque atención médica de inmediato. #StayHome

Laredo ISD les recuerda que practiquen el distanciamiento social.

Para prevenir la propagación de COVID-19 en nuestra comunidad, practique el distanciamiento social:
• Evite salir en público
• Cuando esté en público, mantenga una distancia de seis pies entre usted y los demás.
• Seguir las recomendaciones de los funcionarios locales y estatales.
Obtenga más información en https://texas.gov/covid19
# covid19 #texasfuerte #quedateencasa

post_text:
MEDIA ADVISORY

Due to growing health concerns on COVID – 19 and discussion with Laredo ISD Administration, the Laredo ISD Athletic Department is postponing all non-district athletic related travel and competitions until further notice as a precautionary measure.

Texas Education Agency and the University Interscholastic League have not officially cancelled events, therefore, scheduled District 29-5A and District 29-6A events will be played as scheduled. (District games will be played with VARSITY teams only).

All Middle School Spring sporting events are postponed until further notice as a precautionary measure. Therefore today’s scheduled middle school track and field meet is postponed.

If necessary, updated game schedules will be provided at a later date.

post_text: The LISD Board of Trustees held a ribbon cutting ceremony for the official opening of the new Veterans Field. The new state-of-the-art $6.4 million facility was upgraded with the installation of a new synthetic turf, restrooms, ticket booths, concessions stands, press box, dugout improvements, sports lighting and landscaping. The project was designed by Able City and was built by Leyendecker Construction.

post_text:
No classes for LISD students on February 21, and 24.

Laredo Independent School District campuses and administrative offices will be closed Friday, February 21, due to a district holiday.

However, the LISD Tax Office will remain open on Friday, February 21. The Tax Office is located at 904 Juarez Ave., and will be open during regular business hours, from, 8:00 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.

Also, all Laredo ISD campuses will be closed on Monday, February 24, due to staff development training. LISD administration, faculty, and staff will report to work on Monday morning for their required staff development training.

Classes resume for LISD students on Tuesday, February 25, 2020
